  "prompt": "How does international law intersect with national laws on money laundering?",
  "response": "International law and national laws on money laundering intersect in several important ways:\n\n1. International Conventions and Agreements\n- UN Convention against Transnational Organized Crime\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n- Basel Committee guidelines\n- Establish common standards and principles for combating money laundering\n\n2. Legal Frameworks\n- Countries develop national legislation aligned with international standards\n- Criminalize money laundering activities\n- Establish reporting requirements for financial institutions\n- Create mechanisms for international cooperation\n\n3. Information Sharing\n- Mutual legal assistance treaties\n- Cross-border cooperation between law enforcement agencies\n- Coordinated investigations of complex money laundering schemes\n\n4. Compliance Mechanisms\n- Financial institutions required to implement Know Your Customer (KYC) procedures\n- Mandatory reporting of suspicious transactions\n- International monitoring and evaluation of national anti-money laundering efforts\n\n5. Sanctions and Enforcement\n- International sanctions against countries with weak anti-money laundering frameworks\n- Asset freezing and seizure mechanisms\n- Extradition agreements for money laundering prosecutions\n\n6. Technology and Digital Challenges\n- Addressing cryptocurrencies and digital financial transactions\n- Developing coordinated regulatory approaches\n- Adapting legal frameworks to technological innovations\n\nThese intersections create a comprehensive global approach to preventing money laundering.",
